color: #8b9dc3" target=3D"_blank">deliberately confusing interfaces</a>. Yo=
u=E2=80=99ll only find it when you join Facebook and find that it already u=
nderstands your entire social graph.</div><div style=3D"margin: 0;" class=
=3D"revue-p">It=E2=80=99s a relevant point because the entire Cambridge Ana=
lytica scandal comes down to who decides how our data is used. Zuckerberg t=
estified this week that we should have control over the data Facebook colle=
cts about us. But the most salient point that emerged from his testimony wa=
s that, in fact, we don=E2=80=99t.</div><div style=3D"margin: 0;" class=3D"=
revue-p">Congress was listening. Today a bipartisan group of senators led b=
y Amy Klobuchar (D-MN) and John Kennedy (R-LA) announced they would <a href=
=3D"http://em.getrevue.co/mpss/c/DAE/1EoYAA/t.2gl/Ud2-rwTIQ46KsmIQW7QVCA/h1=
3/dlyCZxOIyB2f4OsrhAw5i4r2WqR-2BwYEEZrozgBL51d1HXHrko9HNeaZG5QmE5pPaHuYD0Ef=
79c6LUUfncwPKLOKuafgsrYy3bippfwHMLOxZltXbqq3nVYVtx-2BF1eF1IWO1t8uMK4jI7L8gS=
-2ByoScA-3D-3D" style=3D"color: #8b9dc3" target=3D"_blank">introduce new le=
gislation designed to protect consumers=E2=80=99 data privacy</a>. Among ot=
her things, the bill would =E2=80=9Censure users have the ability to see wh=
at information about them has already been collected and shared.=E2=80=9D A=
nd if there=E2=80=99s one lesson that emerged from Facebook=E2=80=99s trip =
to Washington, it=E2=80=99s that we don=E2=80=99t know the half of it.</div>
